// Called out
=== INTRO_620 ===
# id: INTRO_620
# mode: day
~ set_header("Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa", "Monday morning")
~ briefing_called_out = true
His eyes meet yours.  For a second — less than a second — the handler isn't there.  Just Robert, a man in his late forties who has been doing this work since before you were in high school, looking at someone he trained.
"I selected you for this assignment because you're the most qualified candidate available," he says.  And it's true.
"But yes."
Two words.  He doesn't elaborate.  He doesn't need to.
~ toast("info", "You saw through Robert's composure.  He trusts you enough to let you.")
