~ set_header("Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa", "Monday morning")
You aren't sure why Robert wanted to meet here instead of just at the office.  Despite the fact that you both worked in the field of the supernatural — sorry, the [url=gloss:NYSE]NYSE[/url] — all you'd done for the past two years since {inciting_incident != "": {inciting_incident}|the incident} was get trained.
Plucked out of your life as a {background != "": {background}|civilian}.  Your government agency didn't officially have a name (everyone just called it the [url=gloss:Branch]Branch[/url]), but it was still absolutely a government agency.  Meaning two years in you were still near the bottom of the pecking order — doing analysis, not going out into the field.
* [You rub your temples and let the thought go.] -> INTRO_105

// Concerns
=== INTRO_322 ===
# id: INTRO_322
# mode: day
~ set_header("Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa", "Monday morning")
"I'm not doing it."
Robert nods once.
"Understood."
He folds the paper before you've finished the sentence and slides it back into his jacket.  He finishes his coffee in two long pulls.
"I'll redirect you to the Vandermeer file when you're back at the office.  Foreign-publication review.  Three months out, minimum."
He stands, leaves a tip that's too generous for the bill, and pays at the till.  At the door he turns.
"You did the right thing telling me now."
He doesn't wait for an answer.
* [Begin again] -> intro_end

