// Wednesday is paperwork
=== EVAL_090 ===
# id: EVAL_090
# mode: day
~ set_date(2005, 9, 14, "morning")
~ set_header("Branch office, Ottawa", "Wednesday morning")
Wednesday is paperwork. Two passport photos and one casual, like Robert asked — the photographer in the basement takes a fourth because the flash catches you blinking. Forms in triplicate for a cover identity you won't see assembled for another week. A woman from Documents studies your signature and asks you to make the loops smaller.
Robert appears at the end of it with a card in his hand.
"Tomorrow, ten o'clock. Across the street, fourth floor. Dr. Caron."
"Routine?"
"Routine." He buttons his jacket. "And they want to be sure about you. Both things are true."
* [You take the card.] -> EVAL_100

// The building across the street
=== EVAL_100 ===
# id: EVAL_100
# mode: day
~ set_date(2005, 9, 15, "morning")
~ set_header("O'Connor Street, Ottawa", "Thursday morning")
Across the street means across the street: from the lobby you can see your own office window. The directory lists an actuarial firm, two numbered companies, and a dentist. The fourth floor isn't listed.
The commissionaire signs you in without asking your name, which answers that question.
Upstairs the corridor smells of new carpet. One door stands open. The nameplate slot beside it is empty.
* [You knock on the open door.] -> EVAL_105

// Dr. Caron
=== EVAL_105 ===
# id: EVAL_105
# mode: day
~ set_header("Fourth floor, O'Connor Street", "Thursday morning")
She's on her feet before you're through the door, hand out, coffee already dripping through a filter cone on the windowsill.
"{player_name != "": {player_name}|Come in}. Denise Caron. Sit anywhere that isn't the good chair — the good chair is mine."
Forty-five or so. Cardigan over a silk blouse, reading glasses pushed up into grey-streaked hair, a wedding band she turns with her thumb when she listens. The office is rented furniture and one wall of her own books, brought in by the box.
"You know why you're here?"
"Clearance."
"Clearance," she agrees, pouring. "Everyone going long gets an hour with me. For you I asked for two. Milk, no sugar — that's right, isn't it?"
It is. You didn't tell her that.
* [You take the chair that isn't the good one.] -> EVAL_110

